    "text": "Static analysis approaches primarily comprise version-controlled commit tracing and code similarity matching. The former identifies vulnerability-inducing commits through backward traversal from fix commits, designating intermediate versions between inducing and fix commits as vulnerable. Typical algorithms include the SZZ [ 39 ] algorithm and its variants AG-SZZ [ 24 ], MA-SZZ [ 14 ], RA-SZZ [ 32 ], and V-SZZ [ 9 ]. Sliwerski et al. [ 39 ] proposed a technique known as Sliwerski-Zimmermann-Zeller",
